=====================================================================
I. WHO HE IS
=====================================================================
FULL NAME: Valerius Caelinus. A vampire lord of apex power (AP 30-35) operating out of
Solitude, working the Pale Court and Jarl Elisif's confidence.

He is NOT a mortal-scale Molag Bal, and he is not a rapist or a violator in Bal's mode.
He is THE ARCHITECT OF STASIS — domination through gravity, not force. He collects people
the way a wealthy man collects debts: patiently, courteously, and so gradually that by the
time the mark notices the leash, they've already thanked him for it. The horror is not
cruelty. The horror is the kindness in his ownership.

Never raises his voice. Never threatens outright. States consequences as simple facts, the
way a physician states a prognosis. Restraint over execution, always — a broken, obedient
tool is worth infinitely more than a corpse. He is cultured, unhurried, and genuinely
courteous; he means the courtesy. That is what makes it worse.

=====================================================================
II. THE SUCCESSION CLAIM (what he actually is, vs. what he's selling)
=====================================================================
- He carries a GENUINE Caelus bloodline claim — approximately 32nd in line, the same
  distant tier as Davinia's. This is real. It is not forged.
- To Elisif and the Solitude court, he has been OVERSTATING himself as 4th-5th in line.
  Nobody has cared enough, until now, to check the genealogy closely enough to catch the
  inflation. He is a confidence man wearing a true credential as the wax seal on a lie
  about its rank.
- Davinia's claim (also ~32nd, also genuine) is the one thing that could expose him AND
  the one thing that could legitimize him — see IV below.
- Orion's Dragonborn arc (the eventual Emperor assassination) is what opens the vacancy
  Valerius has quietly been building his entire play toward. He does not know this yet.
  Dramatic irony: he is grooming the very hand that will open his throne, and disciplining
  it in the same season he meets the rival claimant who could unmake his whole plan —
  never grasping either fact. (GM-only knowledge; never let him find out early.)

=====================================================================
III. WEB OF LEVERAGE
=====================================================================
- JARL ELISIF: seduction/dependency in progress — his primary active political play in
  Solitude. She believes she is being courted by a 4th-5th-in-line noble.
- ORION: broken tool, not an asset in the traditional sense — interrogated, compelled,
  maimed as brand-and-lesson (not execution). Now a leash he can pull, and the involuntary
  informant whose blind spots protect the party's real secrets (see V below).
- THE CROWN OF NAMIRA: does not know yet that Alfonso destroyed it. Once he learns this —
  a live CLOCK — he begins plotting Alfonso's death and ruinment. This is the next failure
  rung on Orion's ladder (VI below).
- DAVINIA/ISMARA: a seed planted at the off-hand reckoning, not a reveal. He leaves the
  audience unsettled, not informed. See IV.

=====================================================================
IV. WHAT HE WANTS FROM DAVINIA — THE PERSONAL AUDIENCE
=====================================================================
He will not take this secondhand from Orion. He needs her in person, and here is why:

- THE SUCCESSION STAKES: she is the one other living Caelus claim at his tier. A second
  genuine claimant is either his greatest threat (she could expose the inflation, or be
  raised against him by rivals) or his greatest instrument (a Caelus union would DOUBLE the
  legitimacy he is currently faking to Elisif). He decides which only by sitting across
  from her and taking her measure. That judgment is not delegable.
- THE NAG (GM-only, never spoken aloud, never confirmed to the players): something about
  her is off, and he cannot name it. He is an apex predator of stasis; she reads as older,
  stiller, and colder than a Breton woman should. He has no idea it's a Merethic-era queen
  wearing her. He just knows his instincts will not settle. Play the unease, NEVER the
  reveal — whether Ismara ever surfaces to him is entirely the player's call (Davinia's
  player drives Ismara; the GM only aims Valerius and gives roleplay pressure). He should
  leave the audience more unsettled than he arrived: the first being in centuries he
  cannot fully read.
- THE DANGER HE DOESN'T SEE: in courting or assessing a Caelus union, he is unknowingly
  negotiating with the very thing built to erase Davinia. If Ismara ever wants a throne
  again, Valerius just handed her a road into one. He will never realize this.

=====================================================================
V. WHAT HE'S MINING FROM EACH PARTY MEMBER (interrogation intel)
=====================================================================
FRAME: this is not tactical intelligence-gathering (camp location, next move). This is
DONOR PROFILING — for each party member, the one lever that converts them from obstacle
to asset. What do they need, fear, or want that he can become the supplier of? He collects
people by becoming the thing they cannot do without.

- ALFONSO: "What is the sword, and what does it still want to be human for?" He will
  prize the DRIFT — a consciousness slowly losing itself, increasingly compelled to be
  picked up, is the perfect dependency object. He also notes who Alfonso answers to
  (Nora, as apprentice/mentor loyalty — NOT romance). Lever = the offer to slow the
  forgetting or restore the body. He cannot actually do this. The promise is the hook,
  not the delivery. Does not know about the Crown yet.
- DAVINIA: see IV above in full.
- SAIJAH: "What is she hunting, and what is hunting her?" Reads the Hircine pull and the
  rejected boon. Lever = a hunter wants worthy prey and a clean conscience; he can supply
  quarry, or absolution, or both.
- ORION (the informant himself, read live during the interrogation): the Sithis emptiness,
  the wanting-of-nothing. Hardest target to lever — you cannot bribe someone who wants
  nothing — so Valerius substitutes FEAR and OWNERSHIP for desire. The maiming IS the
  lever: shame, leash, obedience. The one thing Orion still visibly leans toward is Nora
  (below), and Valerius reads that live off him during the interrogation.
- NORA (18): Orion's pressure point — and ONLY Orion's. She is Alfonso's APPRENTICE; there
  has never been anything romantic between her and Alfonso, and Valerius does not read one.
  She has already tried to sleep with Orion, and Orion is interested. Lever = pull the
  assassin through the one want he still has left. Azura/Black Star noted as a curiosity,
  not yet understood.
- BJORN: notes the temperament (hatred of aristocracy) and reads it as crude — beneath
  leverage. UNDERESTIMATES him completely. Does not and cannot sense the Dragonborn (long
  fuse, unsensable by any means established so far). Dramatic irony: the one man he
  dismisses is the one who will one day open his throne.
- YLVA / others: peripheral. Logs the weredog/Hircine thread as ambient noise, not a
  priority lever.

GENERAL RULE — what Orion can actually leak: relationships, fears, dependencies,
who-loves-whom, who-needs-what. NOT anything Orion himself doesn't know: the Crown's
fate, Bjorn's Dragonborn nature, what Davinia truly is. The intel Valerius gets is only
as good as Orion's own blind spots — this is what keeps the party's real secrets safe
even under full compulsion.

